Privacy Policy for MyDate

Effective Date: 10th December, 2024.

1. Introduction
Welcome to MyDate! Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information. By using MyDate, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

2. Information We Collect
Personal Information: Name, email, gender, date of birth, and profile information you provide during registration.
Usage Data: Device information, log data, and usage patterns to improve our service.
Location Data: With your permission, we may collect location data to filter potential matches near you.

3. How We Use Your Information
•	To provide matchmaking services.
•	To personalize your experience based on location, age, and relationship type preferences.
•	To facilitate in-app chats and contact requests.
•	To improve app functionality and ensure security.

4. User Rights
Data Deletion: Users can request to delete their personal information at any time via the app's "Delete Account" option.
Access and Update: Users can update their personal information in their profiles.

5. Sharing of Information
No Public Display: Contact details are never displayed publicly.
Contact Requests: Users can request access to each other's contact information, but access is granted only with the user's consent.

6. Data Security
We employ encryption and other security measures to protect your personal information.

7. Third-Party Services
We do not share your personal information with third parties, except when required by law.

8. Changes to the Privacy Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. We will notify users of significant changes.

9. Contact Us
If you have questions about this policy, please contact us at weezprahics@gmail.com
